STELLENBOSCH - Stellenbosch University’s Bureau for Economic Research has cut its economic growth forecast for the country for the rest of the year. READ: SA economy shows slight improvement: PMI It's revised its growth estimate down from 1.9 to 1.4 percent. The Bureau says the weaknesses that led to the 2.2 percent contraction in the first-quarter GD, may have continued into the second. READ: SA needs accelerated growth to address poverty and inequality: Nene It's concerned about policy proposals that might not strike a balance between transformation and enabling business growth. A weaker rand and mounting global risks are also cited as reasons behind its revised forecast. eNCA